STATE of North Carolina
v.
Nathaniel LEGGETT. No. 323P05-2. Supreme Court of North Carolina. April 10, 2008. Nathaniel Leggett, Pro Se. John G. Barnwell, Anne M. Middleton, Assistant Attorney Generals, C. Colon Willoughby, Jr., District Attorney, for State of NC.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the petition filed by Defendant on the 5th day of March 2008 in this matter for a writ of certiorari to review the order of the North Carolina Court of Appeals, the following order was entered and is hereby certified to the North Carolina Court of Appeals:

"Dismissed by order of the Court in conference, this the 10th day of April 2008."
